instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The virtual Twin issues control commands back to the PT through the same RabbitMQ broker. The controller component listens on a command queue for “set‑state” messages that specify actuator targets for the heatbed and fan. Upon receiving a command, the controller executes a bang‑bang policy: the heatbed stays ON for the configured heating duration H until the measured temperature rises to the upper limit UL, then the fan drives for the waiting duration C before the heatbed shuts off until the temperature drops to the lower limit LL. The low‑level driver enforces a safe protocol, validates command payloads against the actuator state machine, and, after actuating the devices, publishes the confirmation (e.g., actuator status and timestamps) back to RabbitMQ. Thus the DT’s control logic is continuously validated by feedback data from the PT."
]

